lzh_formatted:
  title: 秋夜雨中
  author: 崔致遠
  language: lzh
  text: 秋風唯苦吟。擧世少知音。䆫外三更雨。燈前萬里心。
korean:
  title: 추야 우중
  author: 최치원
  language: kor
  text: |-
    가을바람에 처량한 이 읊조림만
    온 세상에 지음 적네
    창 밖에는 삼경의 비가 오는데
    등불 앞에 아물아물 만리의 마음이여
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0220_010_0020&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Autumn Rain in the Night
  author: Choi Chi-won
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Autumn wind, and only my mournful song remains.
    The world has few who understand such notes.
    Beyond the window, rain falls at the third watch,
    And before the lamp, my heart stretches ten thousand miles away.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The 'third watch' (삼경) refers to the late hours of night in traditional timekeeping, evoking the poet's solitude in darkness.
  - key: ''
    value: The image of the heart stretching 'ten thousand miles' suggests both physical and spiritual distance—perhaps longing for an absent companion or spiritual kinship.
